In case it's helpful, here is the (almost) analogous Boogie code:

```
function foo(i: int): bool;
function bar(i: int): bool;

procedure test(i:int) returns ()
{  
      assume (forall x: int ::
        { bar(x) }
        (x mod 2 == 0 ==> foo(x))
        && bar(x)
      );
    assert bar(2*i); // passes due to quantifier instantiation
    assert 2*i mod 2 == 0; // makes no difference (passes)
    assert foo(2*i); // fails
}
```

