> Jep is built off of python sub-interpreters which are a rarely used feature of cpython so extension writers often write code that is not compatible with sub-interpreters.

My understanding is that [C-extensions are shared across the sub-interpreters](https://docs.python.org/3/c-api/init.html#c.Py_NewInterpreter), and because of this the exact way to develop with sub-interpreters in mind is a non-trivial affair (and an improvement the subject of a PEP under discussion - https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0554/).

